gl_putchar() - DERP OS man page

Name -------------------
gl_putchar() - puts a character on the scren buffer at the cursor location

Synopsis ---------------

#include "gl_printf.h"

void gl_putchar( char c );

void gl_putchar_at( unsigned int x, unsigned int y, char c );

Description ------------

The gl_putchar function draws a character at the current cursor loccation of 
the user screen buffer. It uses gl.h/draw_character ultimately to draw to 
the screen. The (at) version of this function draws to the provided location
( x, y ).

Return Value -----------

No return value, side effects are a character drawn in the screen buffer.
